parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to fall into the driver's lap, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel falls into the driver's lap
the steering column becomes loose or wobbly
the steering wheel and column fall off
the tilt mechanism "sprungs" causing the wheel to swing up and down
and the vehicle becomes difficult or impossible to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering wheel adjustment pins can cause the steering wheel to wobble or fall into the driver's lap, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel adjustment pins keep falling out
the wheel almost sits on the driver's lap
and the pins have screwdriver marks indicating previous temporary fixes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion steering can cause stiffness in the steering, loss of power steering, and difficulty steering, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The rack and pinion steering becomes stiff in the mornings
makes a whining noise when turned
and feels like there is no power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pads and rotors can cause loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The front brake pads fail frequently
shearing the anti-lock sensor from its mount

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked engine cylinder head can cause coolant or oil leaks, engine stalling, and ultimately lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
A defective coil housing can cause engine misfires, backfiring, and difficulty starting the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Faulty head gaskets can cause coolant or oil leaks, engine stalling, and ultimately lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Oxygen sensor failure can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to accidents or environmental harm.
The failure of the brake system can lead to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: ABS brakes jerk and make a clicking noise
and clunking noises are heard when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the engine to stall, misfire, or fail to start, leading to potential accidents or stranding.
symptoms: gas is present in the oil

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various systems to fail, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Check oil light comes on and off
headlights do not work when hazard lights are used
driver's side window and lock malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine damage, accidents, or stranding.
symptoms: grinding noise is heard from the water pump
and water is heard swishing through the front of the car when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition system failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also lead to fires, which can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: smoke or flames coming from the dashboard area
and occupants being locked in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Starter assembly failure can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In extreme cases, it can also lead to fires, which can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: and smoke or flames coming from the starter area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause a range of problems, including failure to start, stalling, and electrical fires, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: occupants being locked in the vehicle
and fires starting in the steering column.
